  <span id="freeText1988219684234882365" style="display:none">I went through a time in high school when I read nothing but Agatha Christie, setting me up for a lifetime love of mysteries. Thing is I don't remember any of them. I think they were Miss Marple, not Poirot. Now every once in a while I try to sneak in a Christie here and there.<br /><br />For a challenge, I needed a book published in 1953. Poirot was semi-retired then (I think Agatha was about fed up with him after 30 previous books), so his part is small until he gathers everyone together at the end with his surprise reveal of who murdered who. That's always my favorite part. A classic that remains timeless.</span>
